      • initializeDatabase

        public void initializeDatabase(String driver,
                      String url,
                      String username,
                      String password,
                      String isolation,
                      boolean logging,
                      boolean rebuild)
        Initialize the database using the passed arguments
        Parameters:
        driver - Database-driver to use. For example: org.sqlite.JDBC
        url - Location of the database. For example: jdbc:sqlite:{DIR}{NAME}.db
        username - Username required to access the database
        password - Password belonging to the username, may be empty
        isolation - Isolation type. For example: SERIALIZABLE, also see TransactionIsolation
        logging - If set to false, all logging will be disabled
        rebuild - If set to true, all tables will be dropped and recreated. Be sure to create a backup before doing so!
